take him to the nest safely.

00:35.644 --> 00:37.472
Carol: <i>Hey, Daryl.</i>
You sure you're okay?

00:37.472 --> 00:38.777
<i>[Transmission breaking up]
...came back.</i>

00:38.951 --> 00:39.735
Carol: I'm looking
for a friend of mine.

00:39.865 --> 00:40.866
Name's Daryl Dixon.

00:40.997 --> 00:42.390
[Engine revs]

00:42.520 --> 00:43.521
Losang: We need you.

00:43.521 --> 00:44.914
Daryl:
It isn't my fight.

00:45.001 --> 00:46.568
Sometimes, when a person
leaves home,

00:46.655 --> 00:48.526
he comes to find
he belongs someplace else.

00:48.613 --> 00:50.398
Laurent: Daryl!

00:50.485 --> 00:52.139
♪

00:52.313 --> 00:54.097
[Wind whistling,
walkers growling]

00:55.881 --> 00:58.710
[Birds calling]

00:58.710 --> 01:00.973
[Walkers growling]

01:01.061 --> 01:10.418
♪

01:10.505 --> 01:19.470
♪

01:19.557 --> 01:20.471
Help!

01:20.558 --> 01:24.475
♪

01:24.562 --> 01:26.869
