44:09.081 --> 44:11.126
♪

44:11.213 --> 44:13.215
[Walkers growling]

44:13.389 --> 44:17.480
♪

44:22.094 --> 44:28.317
♪

44:28.317 --> 44:30.319
The plane'’s gonna catch.
We got to fly outta here!

44:30.319 --> 44:31.930
Can we just move it?

44:32.060 --> 44:35.716
[Thunder rumbling,
walkers growling]

44:35.716 --> 44:37.109
No, we gotta go.

44:37.109 --> 44:38.240
Now!

44:38.240 --> 44:40.025
Let'’s go!

44:40.155 --> 44:43.028
[Thunder rumbles]

44:43.115 --> 44:46.771
♪

44:46.858 --> 44:48.642
[Man whistles sharply]

44:48.729 --> 44:57.607
♪

44:57.695 --> 45:05.398
♪

45:05.485 --> 45:12.492
♪

45:12.492 --> 45:15.321
Shit.
It didn'’t blow.

45:15.321 --> 45:17.715
We should abort!

45:17.715 --> 45:18.977
What are you doing?!

45:18.977 --> 45:21.196
[Gunshots]
Dixon!

45:21.196 --> 45:22.067
[Screaming] No!

45:22.154 --> 45:27.289
♪

45:27.376 --> 45:30.162
- Let'’s go!
- Alarm! Alarm!

45:30.162 --> 45:32.904
[Gunfire]

45:32.991 --> 45:33.992
♪

45:33.992 --> 45:35.515
[Men shouting]

45:35.602 --> 45:39.911
[Glass shatters, man grunts]

45:39.998 --> 45:41.695
[Walkers growling]

45:41.782 --> 45:44.350
[Thunder rumbles]

45:44.437 --> 45:45.830
Ash: Let'’s go!

45:45.917 --> 45:49.050
[Whispering] Carol...
you'’re gonna do this.

45:49.050 --> 45:52.010
I'’ve never been up
in one of these before.

45:52.010 --> 45:55.013
We'’re gonna have to
clear a path.

45:55.013 --> 45:56.536
There'’s no time.

45:56.536 --> 45:59.017
[Growling]

45:59.757 --> 46:01.236
Grab the tow bar.

46:01.323 --> 46:06.807
♪

46:08.200 --> 46:09.897
♪

46:12.160 --> 46:22.127
♪

46:22.214 --> 46:25.521
[Grunting, panting]

46:25.608 --> 46:27.523
Thank you. Thank you.

46:27.610 --> 46:28.960
Yeah, let'’s
get you home, buddy.

46:29.047 --> 46:31.440
♪

46:31.527 --> 46:34.356
[Woman laughing]

46:34.530 --> 46:44.497
♪

46:44.497 --> 46:46.151
I should have known.

46:46.325 --> 46:50.155
♪

46:50.155 --> 46:52.113
Angels always send
their most vicious demon

46:52.200 --> 46:53.593
to do the dirty work.

46:53.767 --> 46:59.599
♪

46:59.599 --> 47:01.949
And here you are.

47:02.036 --> 47:11.045
♪

47:11.219 --> 47:14.092
♪

47:14.092 --> 47:16.572
[Explosion]

47:16.659 --> 47:25.538
♪

47:25.538 --> 47:27.061
Man: Dixon, come on!

47:27.061 --> 47:30.543
♪

47:30.673 --> 47:32.632
[Walkers growling]

47:32.632 --> 47:34.329
[Thunder rumbling]

47:34.460 --> 47:36.114
[Engine whirring]

47:36.114 --> 47:37.419
Ash: Carol!

47:37.506 --> 47:39.421
[Grunting, shouting]

47:39.421 --> 47:49.127
♪

47:49.127 --> 47:50.650
Let'’s go, let's go.

47:50.650 --> 47:58.223
♪

47:58.397 --> 48:05.839
♪

48:05.926 --> 48:23.857
♪

48:23.944 --> 48:31.212
♪

48:31.299 --> 48:40.047
♪

48:40.221 --> 48:48.142
♪

48:48.142 --> 48:50.623
Ash:
Just center yourself.

48:50.753 --> 48:53.147
Take a deep breath in.

48:53.234 --> 48:54.932
And out.

48:55.062 --> 48:58.587
♪

48:58.587 --> 49:00.285
There'’s nothing to be
afraid of up here.

49:00.459 --> 49:03.201
♪

49:03.331 --> 49:04.680
Look.

49:04.767 --> 49:12.514
♪

49:12.514 --> 49:14.212
[Exhales]

49:14.299 --> 49:21.436
♪

49:21.523 --> 49:27.007
♪

49:38.279 --> 49:40.760
Maybe that's all it was.

49:40.934 --> 49:42.805
Something
that just kept you going.

49:42.805 --> 49:46.200
Two of us together,

49:46.200 --> 49:48.550
it's safer.

49:50.422 --> 49:52.511
Carol: I'm pretty good
at taking care of myself.

49:52.641 --> 49:53.991
Laurent's missing.

49:54.165 --> 49:56.471
Daryl: Someone took him.

49:56.602 --> 49:59.257
I need your help.

49:59.257 --> 50:01.346
People are gonna talk.

50:01.476 --> 50:02.129
Carol: What do you want?

50:05.393 --> 50:09.267
♪

50:14.446 --> 50:16.578
It's only by risking everything
can we find

50:16.709 --> 50:19.059
the true meaning
of faith.

50:19.190 --> 50:20.669
Daryl: What happens
if you're wrong?

50:20.843 --> 50:27.198
♪

50:29.983 --> 50:32.203
Woman: Slate.

50:32.333 --> 50:33.378
Can you guys talk about
bringing Carol back

50:33.508 --> 50:35.380
for the second season?

50:35.510 --> 50:37.947
[Laughs]
[Whistles]

50:38.122 --> 50:39.949
♪

50:40.124 --> 50:41.864
[Explosion]

50:42.039 --> 50:43.475
Hey. What's up?

50:43.649 --> 50:48.828
♪

50:49.002 --> 50:50.177
I love you.

50:50.308 --> 50:51.483
And I love you, too.

50:51.657 --> 50:55.095
♪

50:55.226 --> 50:58.272
Nicotero: I love you, too!
Don't go!

50:58.403 --> 51:00.753
It was interesting when we were
wrapping up "The Walking Dead,"

51:00.883 --> 51:02.624
because at that point,

51:02.755 --> 51:05.671
we left Carol and Daryl
in a good place

51:05.801 --> 51:08.543
so that you would believe
that if anything were to happen,

51:08.717 --> 51:11.111
she would be the one that
would go out looking for him,

51:11.242 --> 51:13.070
which is what we did.

51:13.200 --> 51:15.507
We're supposed
to, like, keep it a secret.

51:15.594 --> 51:18.075
Yeah.
So I was just holed up
in a hotel room.

51:18.205 --> 51:20.164
Oh, yeah, I was... For six weeks.

51:20.338 --> 51:22.035
I was visiting
the Eiffel Tower,

51:22.166 --> 51:23.863
I was going
to restaurants.
[Laughs] Right.

51:23.993 --> 51:24.951
I'm happy
that you're here.

51:25.082 --> 51:27.084
[Crossbow fires]
Aaaah!

51:27.171 --> 51:29.173
Where is he?

51:29.347 --> 51:30.391
They got themselves thrown
on a [bleep]damn boat.

51:30.522 --> 51:32.741
A boat? To where?

51:32.872 --> 51:34.482
[Groans]
To France, okay?

51:36.484 --> 51:39.226
It's been great
being able to have Melissa know

51:39.357 --> 51:40.967
that she's here
and she's playing Carol.

51:41.054 --> 51:43.622
Just getting to see Norman
again, period.

51:43.752 --> 51:45.145
You know, it's fun.

51:45.276 --> 51:48.017
[Engine revs]

51:48.192 --> 51:51.804
I'm here to bring these
two characters together again.

51:51.934 --> 51:54.459
To Carol, Daryl is home.

51:54.589 --> 51:57.418
He is the longest-running
person in her life

51:57.549 --> 51:59.333
since this all started.

51:59.507 --> 52:02.249
And I think she feels
a little lost without him.

52:02.423 --> 52:05.339
I keep thinking about
all the people I left behind.

52:05.470 --> 52:07.298
Wondering if they're
still thinking about me.

52:07.472 --> 52:11.215
The title of episode one is
"La Gentillesse Des EÉtrangers."

52:11.302 --> 52:12.999
That translates as
"The Gentleness of Strangers."

52:13.130 --> 52:15.697
In the show itself,

52:15.828 --> 52:17.482
Daryl has been a stranger in a
strange land from the beginning,

52:17.612 --> 52:19.353
so there is a sense
of sort of strangers

52:19.440 --> 52:21.355
venturing out into the world.

52:21.529 --> 52:22.791
And specifically, though,
that's a line of dialogue

52:22.922 --> 52:25.098
that we hear from Carol

52:25.272 --> 52:27.883
to this man who becomes
a friend, Ash.

52:28.057 --> 52:30.451
I'd like to think
that even still,

52:30.538 --> 52:32.192
we can rely on the kindness
of strangers.

52:32.323 --> 52:34.368
Carol's hoping

52:34.499 --> 52:35.152
that she's gonna be
able to find somebody

52:35.239 --> 52:36.936
who can help her in her journey

52:37.066 --> 52:38.416
to figure out
what's happened to Daryl.

52:38.546 --> 52:40.592
So that's where that title
sort of evolved out of.

52:40.766 --> 52:46.815
♪

52:46.989 --> 52:50.689
Carol is a character,
in the history of the show,

52:50.776 --> 52:53.692
we've seen undergo a lot
of grief and a lot of trauma,

52:53.866 --> 52:56.303
and a lot of that is unresolved.

52:56.434 --> 52:58.958
You know,
when things get quiet enough,

52:59.132 --> 53:01.961
those unresolved issues start
to bubble back up.

53:02.135 --> 53:04.137
And I think that's
really what happened for Carol

53:04.268 --> 53:08.533
when Daryl left and it got
quiet at the Commonwealth.

53:08.663 --> 53:15.801
And I think a big part of this
trip is to resolve those issues.

53:15.931 --> 53:18.630
She thought she had come to
terms with the death of Sophia,

53:18.717 --> 53:21.067
and she had in so many ways.

53:21.154 --> 53:25.289
And her fight for survival
is-- is a tribute to Sophia,

53:25.419 --> 53:28.640
and it always has been.

53:28.727 --> 53:30.511
Nicotero: The season two episode

53:30.642 --> 53:32.731
where Sophia comes out
of the barn--

53:32.861 --> 53:35.429
I remember when we shot it.
I remember everything about it.

53:35.516 --> 53:37.431
McBride: It was
fascinating to me

53:37.562 --> 53:39.303
because those emotions
were right there.

53:39.433 --> 53:42.654
And then the challenge
of keeping it present,

53:42.741 --> 53:44.003
even with the light effects,

53:44.090 --> 53:45.874
like she is still standing there

53:45.961 --> 53:47.354
and this is only going on
in her head,

53:47.485 --> 53:49.704
and yet we're playing it
physically,

53:49.835 --> 53:51.706
was a bit of a challenge.

53:51.793 --> 53:54.231
- And action!
- Sophia!

53:54.361 --> 53:56.450
Nicotero: And I re-created
the same shots

53:56.537 --> 53:59.801
that we had done
on the season two episode.

53:59.932 --> 54:03.936
It was really fun and definitely
took me back to that moment

54:04.066 --> 54:06.243
in a really good way.

54:06.330 --> 54:07.635
Alright, here we go.
And fan!

54:11.813 --> 54:16.253
Nicotero: After spending six
episodes solely based in France,

54:16.383 --> 54:19.604
201 is mostly based
in the United States.

54:19.778 --> 54:22.259
It was a challenge because
we shot it here in France.

54:22.389 --> 54:27.960
So being a farm that looked like
a farm that would have been in,

54:28.134 --> 54:31.093
you know, New England
created a lot of unique hurdles.

54:31.268 --> 54:33.661
[Speaking French]

54:56.380 --> 54:58.251
We're talking
about flying a plane

54:58.382 --> 54:59.774
across the ocean
with no communication,

54:59.905 --> 55:01.646
no weather forecast,

55:01.776 --> 55:04.039
no idea what's waiting
on the other side.

55:04.170 --> 55:06.215
It's my only option.

55:06.346 --> 55:08.000
I couldn't do nothing.

55:08.130 --> 55:10.655
Introducing air travel

55:10.742 --> 55:13.962
in this post-apocalyptic world
feels super profound

55:14.049 --> 55:15.877
and powerful
in this environment.

55:16.008 --> 55:19.054
And getting a plane like this
in the sky,

55:19.185 --> 55:22.667
to fly over the ocean,
is a huge task

55:22.797 --> 55:24.756
because this plane can't even
hold enough fuel to get there.

55:24.843 --> 55:26.235
Zabel: We did a lot
of research on this,

55:26.323 --> 55:28.020
and we talked to experts
on aviation.

55:28.150 --> 55:29.674
And, you know,
it's possible exactly the way

55:29.848 --> 55:32.720
that it plays out in the show,
but it's unlikely,

55:32.851 --> 55:34.853
and there are lots of pitfalls
along the way that--

55:34.983 --> 55:36.637
that you could fall into.

55:36.768 --> 55:38.160
So just the logistics
of that alone

55:38.291 --> 55:39.814
are a big leap of faith
for Carol.

55:39.988 --> 55:41.425
She's done a lot
of scary things,

55:41.599 --> 55:42.991
but she's never gotten on
a plane.

55:43.078 --> 55:45.080
And that's a little
intimidating.

55:45.211 --> 55:48.345
And for Ash, he has found a way
to exist by himself

55:48.475 --> 55:51.478
and be relatively happy
with the memory of his child.

55:51.609 --> 55:54.916
That's a big leap of faith for
him to leave what he's built,

55:55.047 --> 55:57.789
and to leave all the things that
represent his memory of his son.

55:57.876 --> 55:59.138
That's a tough one.

55:59.312 --> 56:00.269
Man: <i>Silence, s'il vous plaît!</i>

56:00.400 --> 56:02.881
One, two...[Popping, hissing]

56:03.011 --> 56:04.578
...three, four!

56:04.665 --> 56:06.450
[Explosion]

56:06.537 --> 56:08.452
Nicotero:
We needed a big finale,

56:08.626 --> 56:12.673
and one of the things
that we talked about was,

56:12.804 --> 56:15.981
well, they gotta drive
the plane through the walkers

56:16.111 --> 56:18.375
to get to the runway.

56:18.462 --> 56:20.159
Carol: Can't we just move it?

56:20.246 --> 56:22.857
Ash: No.
We gotta go-- now!

56:22.988 --> 56:24.729
I have a little bit
of experience flying a plane.

56:24.859 --> 56:27.558
I've flown a plane twice,
a long time ago,

56:27.688 --> 56:29.908
so I had some familiarity
inside the cockpit.

56:30.082 --> 56:31.736
Nicotero: I wanted one gag

56:31.910 --> 56:34.042
where Carol gets attacked
by a walker

56:34.129 --> 56:36.393
and swings it into
the spinning propeller blade.

56:36.480 --> 56:38.830
[Squelching]

56:38.917 --> 56:41.615
My little Indiana Jones homage.

56:41.746 --> 56:43.965
Then it comes time for
them to take off.

56:44.096 --> 56:46.141
With Sébastian,
our stunt coordinator,

56:46.272 --> 56:50.189
I said, "Well,
how can we do this and be safe?"

56:50.363 --> 56:52.060
And he said,
"Oh, no, it'll be fine.

56:52.147 --> 56:53.714
We'll just have the stunt people

56:53.845 --> 56:55.673
get hit by the wing
and fall down."

56:57.457 --> 56:59.372
I never would have imagined

56:59.546 --> 57:01.766
that we would have been
able to do that,

57:01.896 --> 57:04.464
but the stunt team did
a fantastic job

57:04.595 --> 57:06.640
of keeping everybody safe

57:06.814 --> 57:09.077
and giving us some
really spectacular footage.

57:09.208 --> 57:10.470
It all looked great.

57:10.644 --> 57:13.995
[Engines whirring]

57:14.126 --> 57:15.693
There's nothing to be afraid of
up here.

57:24.528 --> 57:41.980
♪

57:42.067 --> 57:51.729
♪
